e1: HH has borderline OR poor FCS
e2: Food expenditure share of total expenditure is > 65%
e3: HH has moderate to severe (2 - 6) Household Hunger Score

of households were found to have a Food Security LSG and to 
be vulnerable
i1: HH does not have access to improved water source
i2: HH doesn't have enough water for drinking OR cooking OR personal hygiene
i3: HH does not have access to an improved santiation facility
i4: HH is treating their water prior to drinking

of households were found to have a WASH LSG and to 
be vulnerable
g1: HH reporting that there is no health clinic or hospital within a one hour's walk from dwellings
g2: HH doesn't have access to specialized reproductive health services
g3: HH spending more than 20% of total expenditure on healthcare
g4: HH is reporting difficulties when trying to access health services in the past 3 months

of households were found to have a Health LSG and to 
be vulnerable
h1: HH is reporting more than one shelter improvement
h2: HH is reporting needing at least one NFI
h3: HH is living in critical shelter

of households were found to have a Shelter LSG and to

b1: At least one member reporting lots of difficulties or cannot do at all in at least one domain
b2: HH is headed by a single female

b5: HH is reporting security/safety concerns as a main barrier for return (fear/trauma associated with AoO, lack of security forces, presence of explosive hazards, fear of discrimination, lack of safety and security for women)
